HELP REV_N                                      Steve Knight, 20 Oct 91

    rev_n( ITEM1, ..., ITEMn, n ) -> ( ITEMn, ..., ITEM1, n )

This procedure reverses the order of the top n items of the stack.  It is
usually used used in the following way

    rev_n(#| EXPR |#)

For example,

    rev_n(#| 1, 2, 3, 4 |#) =>
    ** 4 3 2 1 4
